President Biden delivered a speech at the Belmont Water Treatment Plant in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, highlighting the importance of clean water and the progress being made in rebuilding America's infrastructure. He emphasized that every American deserves access to clean drinking water and discussed the issue of lead pipes and fixtures, which pose a health hazard, particularly affecting low-income families and communities of color. President Biden announced the allocation of $15 billion in funding specifically for the removal of lead pipes, with Pennsylvania already receiving $240 million for water system upgrades. He also mentioned a $340 million loan that will be used to replace service lines and distribution mains. President Biden emphasized the need for this infrastructure work to be done with American workers and products, using union labor. He concluded by expressing his optimism about America's future and the country's ability to lead the world.